te/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-05-27t12:12:13z","updated_at":"2013-05-27t12:15:18z","body":"oh, i read #3054 now, and can see why this was done.\r\n\r\nbasically, it seems updater.php returns two versions: \"5.0.8 owncloud 5.0.6\", where internal version = 5.0.8 (used to trigger database updates), and human readable release version = owncloud 5.0.6.\r\n\r\nthey used to be in sync but not anymore, and that desync was required because of the accident in bug #3054 where the database version had been accidentally bumped by 1 which meant that all future updates would need to keep bumping it higher than the actual release number, to continue to trigger the databaseupdate script.\r\n\r\nokay... the strange version check strings make sense now. i'll update my own version check code to use the \"owncloud 5.0.6\" versionstring as its reference instead."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18495872","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/3485#issuecomment-18495872","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3485","id":18495872,"user":{"login":"tanghus","id":533222,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/e625b634822713b2e346ff7c67d26775?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f6d9c90af1c12f5a88e4d5f216bbc1979.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"e625b634822713b2e346ff7c67d26775","url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus","html_url":"https://github.com/ta