i.github.com/users/tanghus/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-05-27t12:20:31z","updated_at":"2013-05-27t12:20:31z","body":"or just an integer value to increment when updates need to be triggered."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18496090","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/3485#issuecomment-18496090","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3485","id":18496090,"user":{"login":"karlitschek","id":867445,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/87ce2b4531ee1a0c32b50e0d8f049224?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f06e7098636caebfc9c30c9f52eb905df.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"87ce2b4531ee1a0c32b50e0d8f049224","url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek","html_url":"https://github.com/karlitschek","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-05-27t12:24:32z","updated_at":"2013-05-27t12:24:32z","body":"agreed. it is in fact an integer value that is incremented when updates need to be triggered. ;-) i hope people understand this once it more different than the version number."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18498257","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/3485#issuecomment-18498257","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3485","id":18498257,"user":{"login":"tanghus","id":533222,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/e625b634822713b2e346ff7c67d26775?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f6d9c90af1c12f5a88e4d5f216bbc1979.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"e625b634822713b2e346ff7c67d26775","url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus","html_url":"https://github.com/tanghus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-05-27t13:20:20z","updated_at":"2013-05-27t13:20:20z","body":"it just bears too much resemblance with a version number when it's in the `(5, 80, 03)` form, and some update procedures apparently shows it to the user/admin, at least in the log."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18510434","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/3485#issuecomment-18510434","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3485","id":18510434,"user":{"login":"aitte","id":3189852,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/222344b0852d100f34b207390f7d8d26?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f1abbf22286a5ca81b6a0c667329cd9f5.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"222344b0852d100f34b207390f7d8d26","url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte","html_url":"https://github.com/aitte","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitte/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-05-27t18:40:18z","updated_at":"2013-05-27t18:41:40z","body":"@tanghus: i am not even involved with owncloud yet i'll chime in with +1, that's just so much more logical.\r\n\r\ncurrently, i have incorporated updater.php into my email notification script which alerts me when software is outdated on my servers. the updater.php script returns an xml file with these values:\r\n\r\n    <?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\r\n    <owncloud>\r\n      <version>5.0.8</version>\r\n      <versionstring>owncloud 5.0.6</versionstring>\r\n      <url>http://download.owncloud.org/community/owncloud-5.0.6.tar.bz2</url>\r\n      <web>http://owncloud.org/</web>\r\n    </owncloud>\r\n\r\nthey used to be in sync so i assumed version was the machine-readable version and versionstring was the full product name, and therefore i ended up using the version-tag. turns out that's just the internal version which was the cause of the confusion.\r\n\r\nperhaps the official release date could be used for the \"should we update the database?\" purposes instead. like:\r\n\r\n    <?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\r\n    <owncloud>\r\n      <releasedate>2013-05-14</releasedate>\r\n      <version>5.0.6</version>\r\n      <versionstring>owncloud 5.0.6</versionstring>\r\n      <url>http://download.owncloud.org/community/owncloud-5.0.6.tar.bz2</url>\r\n      <web>http://owncloud.org/</web>\r\n    </owncloud>\r\n\r\nif that messes with betatesters (since no release date is known yet at that time), perhaps something else can be used, like a temporary date in the future, or a manually incremented integer, one for each new release/beta?\r\n\r\n    <?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\r\n    <owncloud>\r\n      <release>21</release>\r\n      <version>5.0.6</version>\r\n      <versionstring>owncloud 5.0.6</versionstring>\r\n      <url>http://download.owncloud.org/community/owncloud-5.0.6.tar.bz2</url>\r\n      <web>http://owncloud.org/</web>\r\n    </owncloud>\r\n\r\nanyway, thanks for clearing up the confusion earlier."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18644487","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/3485#issuecomment-18644487","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3485","id":18644487,"user":{"login":"cameronbrister","id":1434885,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/4f3cd9463234266bc7fc4372e3c315e9?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2ff80013edb18f6dce19d57a807bc1ed13.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"4f3cd9463234266bc7fc4372e3c315e9","url":"https://api.github.com/users/cameronbrister","html_url":"https://github.com/cameronbrister","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cameronbrister/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cameronbrister/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cameronbrister/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cameronbrister/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cameronbrister/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cameronbrister/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cameronbrister/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cameronbrister/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cameronbrister/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-05-29t20:38:59z","updated_at":"2013-05-29t20:38:59z","body":"agreed - the internal version number shouldn't resemble the actual version number."}]